<br>
The one thing I wanted to point out that although I really do believe Druids need help they don't need as much help they are asking for in their petition.  If you believed their petition they are completely helpless. ^_^<br>
<br>
I really do believe that you can't ask for it all.  Asking for massive heals and massive damage is wrong.  Or at the very least gives less creditablity and appears more like a &quot;class whine&quot;.<br>
<br>
Caster damage in general seems broken.  Unless you are a Wizard you often have hard times getting your damage to stick.  If this doesn't seem odd to you think about the new Cazic-Thule.  We as Paladins are having known issues with just stunning them.  At least we can still beat up the monster with our melee.  Where would a class with their primary mode of damage being their spells do?  Hopefully if Verant delivers on their promise to help Casters out in general this problem will go away (or probalby change into something more workable).<br>
<br>
I forgot who said it here but healing is all about efficiency.  NT is kind of clunky as is for 880 HP for 400 mana(remember CC is 775 HP for 225 mana &quot;by the book&quot;).  I wouldn't mind it at all if it was tweaked to be more timely and/or mana efficient.<br>
<br>
However I don't think Druids are really going to enjoy a group heal and a better NT and a HOT. ^_^ Ask any Cleric.  They have *a lot* of good heals and they can only afford the time and slots to do some.  Druids should try to pick one type.  I'm behind fixing up NT because that would give them a niche in raids.  Looking after non-tank hit points would be an interesting job to take on I believe and giving them a viable point heal would work great.<br>
<br>
Also keep the amount of trolling and flaming down if you visit Druids Grove.  There is their share of &quot;anti-pov&quot; but there are also those who are open minded.  I want to see Druids get fixed up and not get flustered if their attempt to draw attention falls flat.<br>
<br>
And if you are a Druid reading this please be proud but be humble. ^_^ <p><font size="+1">
Aeka<br>
Level 60 Paladin on Povar<br>
