<br>
I have always been a grouping druid and played with my husband's cleric since lvl 1. I have always thought it was unfair that druid and shaman can sow, but that cleric can't, after all, they are all priest class. And I think the post50 game is and always been broken to a certain extent as far as class balance, I think all classes find that the game changes for them and that a great deal of boring raids is part of the endgame instead of just experience hunts.<br>
<br>
I am pretty happy with my role as backup healer in a group, as often as not I am healing the chanter and other casters, but sometimes I am slapping on a heal on a tank because the CH isn't going to hit in time. I also have my nukes and I am often enough grouped where we are missing either a chanter or a shaman, where I am using spells like DS or str buffs that I would otherwise not be asked for.<br>
<br>
I think the thing that has come up for me more than anything else the whole time I've been a druid is that I have a whole bunch of spells that are outdoor only, while a lot of the cool places in the game are indoor dungeons. It would have been nice to try harmony in one of those dungeons.<br>
<br>
I have paladin friends who are now happily making money doing rezzes for donations, and I don't begrudge them a bit of it, there were never enough clerics around to do all the rezzing, I only wish they had gotten it sooner. Thanks to all in this thread who have said that not all druids are a$$holes and that not all a$$holes are druids.<br>
