<br>
The important distinction that needs to be made for druids is raid vs non-raid.<br>
<br>
Currently, non-raid... druids are fine.  A few things would be nice, like the Nexus port.  The epic effect isn't super useful... but then, only a few really are.  They tend to be healers... that and snare are why they get added to groups, SoW at lower levels.  Their dots are hard to resist and provide plenty of damage.  Groupwise, they can keep a group healed.  Not as well as a shaman, but that's because the shaman can slow.  Give the druid a slower though and you are fine.  CH is simply not necessary.  Without CH though, you are better off with a slightly more melee heavy group and dividing damage so that regen is most effecient.<br>
<br>
I run a paladin/enchanter combo.  With that, the paladin pulls, heals, buffs (all but symbol, though AC buff comes from BP), and fights.  He doesn't sit and med.  Matter of fact, adding a shaman or cleric to my group is less effecient in many areas because the healing/slowing power isn't needed.<br>
<br>
But on raids... here druids suffer.  A druid isn't a wizard.  And a druid isn't a cleric.  Wizards do insane damage.  They get resisted less and have a much better selection of nukes to choose from with AA abilities that help them out.  Clerics have complete heal.  Now, druids do get a couple of useful buffs/debuffs.  But that's a 1 druid job.  All the rest spend their time not being wizards or clerics.<br>
<br>
Do I think druids should get a group heal?  No.  No way.  This ability is what makes paladins very nice on raids.  Give it to druids and paladins suffer.  The wrong class to cut into for raid desirability.<br>
<br>
I do think that druids need an improvement in healing.  Single target healing.  Because it is the cleric who's must have factor needs to be cut in to.  The first change to make would be to lower the level 60 heal to 57 or 58.  The second would be something to cut into the CH dependency.<br>
<br>
A percentage heal would be nice, if Verant's engine can handle that (which I doubt... notice CH is 10k, not 100%).  So assuming that isn't possible, something like a 2800 point heal, 10 second cast, 400 mana, at level 60.  It's a nice heal, 7:1 effecient.  But not enough to heal a main tank from the pummelling of a major mob.  What this means is that it takes 2 druids to equal 1 cleric on a raid in the healing role.<br>
<br>
Does this hurt the desirability of clerics in xp groups?  Probably.  You already don't need clerics in many areas.  Giving druids a better heal makes them more desirable.  Should clerics be compensated for it?  That's another question.  And the answer is yes.  Don't ask me exactly how... but it should be something that gives them some versatility in xp groups, without touching upon their raid desirability.  Another option would be to make this druid heal take a pearl each cast.  A minor cost for a raid.  But adds up fast for xp groups.  That way, the druid heal becomes a big boss mob heal only. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=15171.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=15171.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15171.topic&index=60><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=15171.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=15171.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=15171.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=15